<br>
Ive noticed a few trends of popular items in the Bazaar lately, and ive often wondered what you all have found to be the most successful &quot;Regular&quot; sells.  Some items like tradeskill supplies, PoTC earring quest pieces, and several other items seem to be fairly consistant, but on the other hand, I havent actually tried my hand at making money off of some of those items.<br>
<br>
My question is this: What have you all found to be some of your more successfull sells in the bazaar, based on difficulty of getting yourself/making yourself, as well as what has been the most consistant?<br>
<br>
If you sold something once or twice it doesnt really constitute a consistant sale, so what have you found to &quot;always&quot; be a money maker?<br>
<br>
Thanks for the tips.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saynac>Saynac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 6:20:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8982.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Money Making for the Mage in the Bazaar</span><hr size=1> I can always sell bone chips for 12pp a stack in the bazaar, they go quick too. I think it costs about 3gp to buy a stack off of a NPC vendor. Not a big amount of money, but it adds up over time.<br>
<br>
The other easy sure-seller is Mt. Death Mineral Salts and Green Goblin Skin. Search NPC vendors and you'll find this everywhere -- it is usually on lots of FV vendors though. You can sell one of each for 20-50pp, depending on your market. So a stack will get you a couple hundred plat.<br>
<br>
Sell summoned lev rings for a couple plat each. People always buy those. If you are 60+, sell the PoP summoned weapons. <p>-Saynac</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 6:57:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8982.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Money Making for the Mage in the Bazaar</span><hr size=1> Leather padding is my main niche.  I can usually sell it within 5 minutes of going into trader mode at 25pp a piece (EDIT 500pp a stack).  Since LoY, the market has been notably slower.  I guess because tradeskillers are still exploring.<br>
<br>
High/med/low quality pelts always sell, as does spider/spiderling/shade silk.<br>
<br>
I will also tell you what doesn't sell: 50- mage spells. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I decided to use my research for the power of good, and made 3 complete sets of research-only spells for lvls 16-49.  I know it would have been a wonderful thing when I hit those levels to find all the spells I need.<br>
<br>
I scoured the world, and found a good cache of the words and supplies for what I needed. Went to OOT for the 20 pets for research, then went to the Qeynos mage guild, sat down in front of the vendors, and completed the sets.<br>
<br>
They have been rotting in my trader satchels for over a week now.  I think I sold all the 49 pets, 1 29 water pet, and all of the everfounts.  Nothing else has sold.  Prices were 15-50pp, which is fair for the time and cost involved.   <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A> at: 3/7/03 8:09:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goramus>Goramus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 7:11:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8982.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Money Making for the Mage in the Bazaar</span><hr size=1> If Im still semi-awake at the end of a long day of playin I try to make a bunch of sets of our pet gear. They sell quickly at 10p per item, usually I am all sold out by the morning. Ive had people send me tells that I should do it more often. It doesnt make alot of pp but its enough to cover my C3 addiction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 9:57:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8982.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Money Making for the Mage in the Bazaar</span><hr size=1> I make a decent amount of plat selling my summoned focus items and pet enhancing summons. I can sell the 61 bracer and earring for 100pp each, the 50s bracer and earring for 75pp, rings, elemental blanket, for 50pp each, and pet stuffs for about 25pp each. I can make 300-500pp a night selling something that takes me 5 minutes to summon up. Now I do agree that the prices are high, but since the summons are lore, and I won't be able to either summon a bunch extra or restock during the night, it's in my best interest to leave them a bit high. They will sell. Sometimes they sell before I've medded the mana back, and I have to resummon multiple times before I can log for the night. <br>
<br>
I guess being on a server with few high level mages pays off.<br>
<br>
<br>
Other constant sellers for me are tradeskill supplies for people who are powerskilling, PoTC items, and Opal steins (thank god, since I make so many of them anyways for skill ups). I also keep my eyes peeled for high demand items, and if I see someone trying to sell one off quick I'll grab it a bit lower than going rate as I have the luxery of a trader that's on nearly 24 hours a day and I can afford to wait for a buyer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=8982.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=8982.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8982.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.threadControl?topicID=8982.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8982.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8982.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements"